09/02/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Visiting Eurogroup President Jean-Claude Juncker predicted on Tuesday (February 8th) that the "euro will survive and Greece will survive thanks to the euro". Following a meeting with Prime Minister George Papandreou in Athens, Junker added "There can be no speaking of â¦ [Greece] leaving the Eurozone." Papandreou said that his government "received a mandate from the Greek people to proceed with major reforms, and that is what we do". (ANA-MPA, To Vima, Nafthemporiki - 08/02/11)
